The paper discusses watermarking techniques for relational databases, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The preservation of query outputs is a key concern in watermarking, which is a security issue and falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of graph theory and logical formulas, which are topics in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the adaptation of techniques for watermarking, which involves information theory (cs.IT).
